This paper discusses the design and evaluation of network architectures for information-centric networks, which are focused on content distribution rather than host-to-host communication. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including network architecture (cs.NI), distributed computing (cs.DC), security and privacy (cs.SI), cryptography (cs.CR), and computational complexity (cs.CC). However, given the focus on network architecture and performance, cs.NI is the most likely category, followed by cs.DC and cs.SI.
